      "content": "You can calculate your bolus by taking your current reading of 185, subtracting your target of 100 to get a difference of 85, and then dividing that difference by your sensitivity factor (e.g., 85 divided by 10 equals 8.5 units). Since you are a math person, you should also account for insulin on board by checking your pump or syringe to subtract any units currently active before administering your dose. Finally, remember to eat the meal immediately after taking the insulin to prevent hypoglycemia while the medication works its magic.",
